{"id": "1512512298890170492", "channel_id": "1496819686699040860", "author_id": "1198497578703126648", "author_name": "glitzy_x", "content": "hello everynyan. i was going to make five fanarts for good luck since doresain is coming very soon, but quickly realized my artblock was not going to let me. have one self indulgent sketch and five cannibalism fun facts intead (one for each copy i need for AA): \n\n\n1. some of the first documented cases of medicinal cannibalism may have arisen due to a mistranslation, mistaking an herb for mummified remains. \n2. doresain himself rarely names the necrovian tradition as \"cannibalism\". instead, he uses the term \"necrophagy\" because cannibalism implies the act of killing the individual, while necrophagy is simply the act of feeding on the individual of the same species.\n3. following the same theme, doresain engages in several kinds of cannibalism/necrophagy: gastronomic cannibalism (doing it for the taste), exocannibalism (eating your enemies either as an act of domination or respect), and endocannibalism (consuming dead relatives/members of your community) \n4. kuru disease! this is a fatal neurodegenerative disease caused by misfolded prions. you can get it if you eat infected brain tissue, and was most known because it broke out in papa new guinea cause of the whole endocannibalism thing. if you somehow have a specific antibody that guards against kuru then your ancestors probably ate people. \n5. there is currently no law that explicitly forbids cannibalism. if anything, you would only be punished by law for tampering with the dead body.", "timestamp": "2026-06-05T17:43:53.175000+00:00", "thread_id": "1496819686699040860", "edited_timestamp": "2026-06-05T17:45:16.710000+00:00", "reactions": [{"emoji": "🔥", "emoji_id": null, "count": 2}], "attachments": [{"id": "1512512298642575570", "filename": "IMG_20260605_235402_394.jpg", "content_type": "image/jpeg", "size": 686192, "url": "https://cdn.discordapp.com/attachments/149